A '''sum certain''' is a specified and set amount of money owed by one person to another. It is a legal [[term of art]], having specialized meaning in the law. Some kinds of legal claims can not be brought at all unless the sum certain can be plead. A document claimed to be a [[negotiable instrument]] can not be negotiated unless it is for a sum certain.
==External links== *{{cite web|url=http://law.onecle.com/new-york/uniform-commercial-code/UCC03-106_3-106.html|title=Section 3-106 - Sum Certain|date=15 August 2006|work=New York Uniform Commercial Code Law|accessdate=4 January 2010}}
[[Category:Legal terminology]] [[Category:Debt]] [[Category:Negotiable instrument law]]

'''Syahril Sabirin''' (born 14 October 1943 in [[Bukittinggi]], [[West Sumatra]]) served as the Governor of [[Bank Indonesia]] from 1999 to 2003, succeeding [[J. Soedradjad Djiwandono|Soedrajad Djiwandono]]. 

Before joining Bank Indonesia, Syahril studied at [[Gadjah Mada University]] in [[Yogyakarta]], graduating with an economics degree from the Faculty of Economics in the university.

In 2000 he was arrested in a fraud scandal surrounding Bank Bali.<ref>{{cite news | title = Baligate, and Why It Matters; Indonesia's Recovery, and Democrac, Tested by Scandal | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1999/09/29/business/baligate-and-why-it-matters-indonesia-s-recovery-and-democracy-tested-by-scandal.html | publisher = [[The New York Times]] | date = 1999-09-29 | accessdate = 2018-07-19}} and {{cite news | title = Indonesian Bank Investigation | url = https://www.nytimes.com/2000/06/22/business/world-business-briefing-asia-indonesian-bank-investigation.html | publisher = [[The New York Times]] | date = 2000-06-22 | accessdate = 2009-06-11}}</ref> Sabirin had initially been sentenced to three years in prison in 2002, a sentence which the [[Indonesian Supreme Court|Supreme Court]] reduced to two years in 2009.<ref>{{cite news | title = Ex-Indonesia central bank chief receives 2 years | url = https://www.forbes.com/feeds/ap/2009/06/11/ap6532783.html | publisher = [[Forbes]] | agency = [[Associated Press]] | date = 2009-06-11 | accessdate = 2009-06-11}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>


